00:34:37.535 --> 00:34:40.496
Oh, Daniel-san,
happy Halloween. You like?

778
00:34:40.496 --> 00:34:41.997
Yeah, that's nice.

779
00:34:41.997 --> 00:34:44.458
How school today?
Lot's happening.

780
00:34:46.502 --> 00:34:48.920
What's the matter?
You not going?

781
00:34:48.920 --> 00:34:50.672
DANIEL:
Nah.

782
00:34:50.672 --> 00:34:52.424
How come?

783
00:34:52.424 --> 00:34:54.676
I'm not into dancin' that much.

784
00:34:56.136 --> 00:34:57.888
I don't feel like it, anyway.

785
00:34:57.888 --> 00:35:03.227
Oh, Daniel-san, you too
much by self. Not good.

786
00:35:03.227 --> 00:35:08.106
I'm not by myself.
I'm with you.

787
00:35:08.106 --> 00:35:09.774
To make honey, young bee

788
00:35:09.774 --> 00:35:12.236
need young flower,
not old prune.

789
00:35:13.487 --> 00:35:16.198
I don't have a costume, anyway.

790
00:35:16.198 --> 00:35:20.077
If have costume, you go?

791
00:35:20.077 --> 00:35:22.996
Yeah, maybe if I went
as the invisible man.

792
00:35:22.996 --> 00:35:26.208
"Invisible man"?

793
00:35:26.208 --> 00:35:28.293
Yeah, you know,
so no one would see me.

794
00:35:29.378 --> 00:35:30.462
Oh.

795
00:35:32.297 --> 00:35:36.843
<i>♪ Lookin' for you
Impatiently ♪</i>

796
00:35:36.843 --> 00:35:40.805
<i>♪ Past hasn't been
Easy for me ♪</i>

797
00:35:40.805 --> 00:35:45.018
<i>♪ I've been so far away ♪</i>

798
00:35:45.018 --> 00:35:46.395
Hey, there's Daniel.

799
00:35:46.395 --> 00:35:47.563
Where?

800
00:35:47.563 --> 00:35:48.688
The shower.

801
00:35:48.688 --> 00:35:49.773
How do you know?

802
00:35:49.773 --> 00:35:51.691
I just know. May I?

803
00:35:53.277 --> 00:35:55.070
Don't know what she sees in him.

804
00:35:55.070 --> 00:35:57.030
She must be into fungus.

805
00:35:59.199 --> 00:36:01.659
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh ♪</i>

806
00:36:01.659 --> 00:36:04.329
ALI: Help me! Help me.
My flower needs water!

807
00:36:06.039 --> 00:36:09.751
Hey, you've come
to the right place, stranger.

808
00:36:09.751 --> 00:36:11.711
Yeah, I've never danced
in a shower before.

809
00:36:11.711 --> 00:36:12.879
A friend of mine made this.

810
00:36:12.879 --> 00:36:14.089
It's fun.

811
00:36:14.089 --> 00:36:15.257
Isn't it great?

812
00:36:15.257 --> 00:36:17.259
So where have you been hiding?

813
00:36:17.259 --> 00:36:19.219
Well, I haven't been hiding.

814
00:36:19.219 --> 00:36:20.845
Oh, I haven't seen you around.

815
00:36:20.845 --> 00:36:22.222
You been lookin'?

816
00:36:22.222 --> 00:36:23.307
Sort of.

817
00:36:23.307 --> 00:36:24.766
Sort of?

818
00:36:24.766 --> 00:36:27.478
I thought maybe
you were still angry with me.

819
00:36:27.478 --> 00:36:28.979
Why?

820
00:36:28.979 --> 00:36:30.981
Well, because of what I said
last time I saw you.

821
00:36:30.981 --> 00:36:33.024
Oh, no, no. I've been
thinking a lot about that.

822
00:36:33.024 --> 00:36:34.568
No, I know.
But I should really learn

823
00:36:34.568 --> 00:36:36.194
to mind my own business.

824
00:36:36.194 --> 00:36:38.738
No. I think you're right
about facing things head-on.

825
00:36:38.738 --> 00:36:40.240
I feel the same way.

826
00:36:40.240 --> 00:36:42.451
I just forgot for a while.

827
00:36:42.451 --> 00:36:44.202
Thanks for reminding me.

828
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:47.414
[CHUCKLING]
You're welcome.

829
00:36:47.414 --> 00:36:48.999
It's just that he thinks
he can do

830
00:36:48.999 --> 00:36:50.542
whatever he wants to people.

831
00:36:50.542 --> 00:36:51.502
Who?

832
00:36:51.502 --> 00:36:53.253
Johnny.
Oh.

833
00:36:53.253 --> 00:36:55.339
I'd love to see him get a dose
of his own medicine.

834
00:36:55.339 --> 00:36:56.465
Well, you know,

835
00:36:56.465 --> 00:36:57.966
what goes around comes around.

836
00:36:57.966 --> 00:36:59.717
Yeah, I'd love to be there
when it does.

837
00:36:59.717 --> 00:37:01.970
[CHUCKLING]
Me too.

838
00:37:01.970 --> 00:37:03.763
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

839
00:37:07.058 --> 00:37:09.144
So, you want to go outside?

840
00:37:09.144 --> 00:37:10.979
[CLICKING TONGUE]

841
00:37:10.979 --> 00:37:12.230
You talked me into it.

842
00:37:12.230 --> 00:37:13.565
[CHUCKLING]

843
00:37:15.526 --> 00:37:18.111
[IMITATING CHICKEN]

844
00:37:18.111 --> 00:37:20.531
Check out this chicken.
He's wild!

845
00:37:20.531 --> 00:37:22.240
That guy's using real eggs.

846
00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:23.575
He's great.

847
00:37:24.201 --> 00:37:25.285
No! No!

848
00:37:25.285 --> 00:37:26.828
[ALL LAUGHING]

849
00:37:32.501 --> 00:37:33.918
Johnny.

850
00:37:33.918 --> 00:37:34.961
[TOILET FLUSHING]

851
00:37:34.961 --> 00:37:36.463
[BANGING ON DOOR]

852
00:37:38.131 --> 00:37:39.257
Johnny.

853
00:37:43.637 --> 00:37:44.846
Got the number rolled yet?

854
00:37:44.846 --> 00:37:46.014
In a minute.

855
00:37:46.014 --> 00:37:47.057
I'm gonna get the guys.

856
00:37:47.057 --> 00:37:48.600
Okay.
Hey, hurry up.

857
00:38:08.953 --> 00:38:10.872
<i>[MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]</i>

858
00:38:44.782 --> 00:38:45.783
[WATER RUNNING]

859
00:38:45.783 --> 00:38:47.075
JOHNNY:
Shit!

860
00:38:47.075 --> 00:38:48.535
Hey, man.

861
00:38:48.535 --> 00:38:49.911
DANIEL:
Move, man!

862
00:38:54.625 --> 00:38:56.543
Hey, Johnny, what's up?

863
00:38:59.129 --> 00:39:02.215
Get out of the way!
Get out of the way! Look out!

864
00:39:02.215 --> 00:39:03.592
Daniel, what-what's wrong?

865
00:39:03.592 --> 00:39:05.885
It's comin' around.

866
00:39:05.885 --> 00:39:07.429
[JOHNNY YELLING]

867
00:39:10.140 --> 00:39:11.266
[GRUNTING]

868
00:39:11.266 --> 00:39:12.684
Get up!

869
00:39:14.978 --> 00:39:16.647
Get out of my way!

870
00:39:18.649 --> 00:39:20.317
[HONKING]

871
00:39:20.317 --> 00:39:21.985
[TIRES SCREECHING]

872
00:39:24.154 --> 00:39:26.573
MAN:
What the hell are you doing?

873
00:39:27.324 --> 00:39:28.784
Get out of the way!

874
00:39:29.743 --> 00:39:31.244
[JOHNNY GRUNTS]

875
00:39:40.086 --> 00:39:41.505
<i>♪ Danger ♪</i>

876
00:39:42.547 --> 00:39:44.924
<i>♪ Everywhere I turn ♪</i>

877
00:39:44.924 --> 00:39:50.180
<i>♪ No shelter
And the truth is under fire ♪</i>

878
00:39:50.180 --> 00:39:51.849
[PANTING]

879
00:39:51.849 --> 00:39:54.852
<i>♪ There ain't
No lookin' back ♪</i>

880
00:39:54.852 --> 00:39:57.688
<i>♪ You put it all behind ♪</i>

881
00:39:57.688 --> 00:40:00.607
<i>♪ When you're
Runnin' out of time ♪</i>

882
00:40:03.234 --> 00:40:04.319
[GRUNTING]

883
00:40:04.319 --> 00:40:05.987
He ain't goin' over.

884
00:40:06.988 --> 00:40:08.573
[ALL YELLING]

885
00:40:08.573 --> 00:40:09.658
We got him now.

886
00:40:09.658 --> 00:40:10.950
[GRUNTS]

887
00:40:10.950 --> 00:40:12.577
You little wimp.

888
00:40:15.497 --> 00:40:17.541
You couldn't leave
well enough alone,

889
00:40:17.541 --> 00:40:18.876
could you, little twerp?

890
00:40:18.876 --> 00:40:20.585
No, you had to push it.

891
00:40:20.585 --> 00:40:22.253
Now you're gonna pay.

892
00:40:22.253 --> 00:40:23.755
[GRUNTS]

893
00:40:23.755 --> 00:40:26.800
Oh, where are you goin'?

894
00:40:26.800 --> 00:40:29.678
How about a front kick, Johnny?

895
00:40:29.678 --> 00:40:30.846
[GRUNTS]

896
00:40:31.929 --> 00:40:33.014
[GROANS]

897
00:40:33.014 --> 00:40:34.641
Get him up.

898
00:40:34.641 --> 00:40:36.727
BOBBY: Leave him alone,
man. He's had enough.

899
00:40:36.727 --> 00:40:37.977
Shut up, Bobby!

900
00:40:37.977 --> 00:40:39.437
Look at him.
He can't even stand up.

901
00:40:39.437 --> 00:40:40.438
So what?

902
00:40:40.438 --> 00:40:41.899
That don't mean squat.

903
00:40:41.899 --> 00:40:43.941
Johnny, leave him alone.
He's had enough!

904
00:40:43.941 --> 00:40:45.610
I'll decide
when he's had enough, man.

905
00:40:45.610 --> 00:40:47.278
What is wrong with you, Johnny?

906
00:40:47.278 --> 00:40:49.698
The enemy deserves
no mercy. Right!

907
00:40:49.698 --> 00:40:51.032
Right?
Right!

908
00:40:51.032 --> 00:40:53.076
BOBBY:
You're crazy, man!

909
00:40:53.076 --> 00:40:54.327
[YELLING]

910
00:40:57.247 --> 00:40:58.665
Johnny, Bobby, get him!

911
00:40:58.665 --> 00:41:00.041
Yeaaa!

912
00:41:00.041 --> 00:41:01.084
[GRUNTS]

913
00:41:03.294 --> 00:41:04.462
[GROANS]

914
00:41:11.845 --> 00:41:13.137
[GROANING]

915
00:41:15.306 --> 00:41:16.850
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

916
00:41:29.237 --> 00:41:30.572
Daniel-san.

917
00:41:32.073 --> 00:41:33.199
Come.

918
00:41:45.002 --> 00:41:46.129
[GRUNTS]

919
00:41:46.129 --> 00:41:47.672
Now we got you.

920
00:42:15.408 --> 00:42:17.702
Dan, leave on.

921
00:42:17.702 --> 00:42:18.996
It stinks, man.
What is this?

922
00:42:18.996 --> 00:42:20.789
Smell bad, heal good.

923
00:42:20.789 --> 00:42:21.957
[SIGHS]

924
00:42:25.209 --> 00:42:26.711
Hey, where did Spiderman go?

925
00:42:26.711 --> 00:42:28.005
Who?

926
00:42:28.005 --> 00:42:29.673
That guy, that guy
who bailed me out.

927
00:42:29.673 --> 00:42:31.090
Where did he go?

928
00:42:34.427 --> 00:42:35.929
What, you?

929
00:42:38.055 --> 00:42:39.140
No way.

930
00:42:39.140 --> 00:42:40.433
Why no way?

931
00:42:40.433 --> 00:42:41.518
Because... because...

932
00:42:41.518 --> 00:42:43.728
Because, uh, because old man?

933
00:42:43.728 --> 00:42:44.938
[CHUCKLES]

934
00:42:44.938 --> 00:42:47.565
Have tea. Feel better.

935
00:42:54.155 --> 00:42:55.323
[SIGHS]

936
00:43:14.175 --> 00:43:15.760
How come you didn't tell me?

937
00:43:15.760 --> 00:43:17.094
Tell you what?

938
00:43:17.094 --> 00:43:18.763
That you knew karate.

939
00:43:18.763 --> 00:43:20.097
You never ask.

940
00:43:20.097 --> 00:43:21.975
Where'd you learn it from?

941
00:43:21.975 --> 00:43:23.685
Father.

942
00:43:23.685 --> 00:43:26.771
I thought he was a fisherman.

943
00:43:26.771 --> 00:43:29.900
In Okinawa,
All Miyagi know two thing:

944
00:43:29.900 --> 00:43:32.235
Fish and karate.

945
00:43:32.235 --> 00:43:35.906
Karate come from China,
16th century.

946
00:43:35.906 --> 00:43:38.825
Called "te." "hand."

947
00:43:38.825 --> 00:43:44.497
Much later, Miyagi ancestor
call "karate."

948
00:43:44.497 --> 00:43:46.875
"Empty hand."

949
00:43:46.875 --> 00:43:49.168
I always thought it came
from Buddhist temples

950
00:43:49.168 --> 00:43:51.295
and stuff like that.

951
00:43:51.295 --> 00:43:53.090
You have too much TV.

952
00:43:54.507 --> 00:43:56.718
That's what my mother tells me.

953
00:44:00.680 --> 00:44:02.557
Hey, you ever taught anyone?

954
00:44:02.557 --> 00:44:03.683
No.

955
00:44:03.683 --> 00:44:05.351
Would you?

956
00:44:05.351 --> 00:44:06.519
Depend.

957
00:44:06.519 --> 00:44:07.687
On what?

958
00:44:07.687 --> 00:44:09.106
Reason.

959
00:44:09.814 --> 00:44:11.108
How's revenge?

960
00:44:13.902 --> 00:44:16.404
Daniel-san,
you look revenge that way,

961
00:44:16.404 --> 00:44:19.074
start by digging two grave.

962
00:44:19.074 --> 00:44:21.618
Well, at least
I have company, right?

963
00:44:21.618 --> 00:44:26.289
Fighting always
last answer to problem.

964
00:44:26.289 --> 00:44:27.582
Uh, no offense, Mr. Miyaji,

965
00:44:27.582 --> 00:44:29.333
but I don't think
you understand my problem.

966
00:44:29.333 --> 00:44:32.253
Miyagi understand
problem perfect.

967
00:44:33.797 --> 00:44:37.926
Your friend
all karate student, eh?

968
00:44:37.926 --> 00:44:40.428
"Friend"? Oh, yeah,
those guys.

969
00:44:40.428 --> 00:44:42.680
Problem, attitude.

970
00:44:42.680 --> 00:44:45.266
No, problem is I'm getting
my ass kicked every other day.

971
00:44:45.266 --> 00:44:46.392
That's the problem.

972
00:44:46.392 --> 00:44:49.938
Because boys have bad attitude.

973
00:44:50.939 --> 00:44:53.274
Karate for defense only.

974
00:44:54.734 --> 00:44:57.194
That's not
what these guys are taught.

975
00:44:57.779 --> 00:44:59.781
I can see.

976
00:44:59.781 --> 00:45:01.866
No such thing bad student.

977
00:45:01.866 --> 00:45:03.952
Only bad teacher.

978
00:45:03.952 --> 00:45:06.287
Teacher say, student do.

979
00:45:07.622 --> 00:45:09.666
Oh, great. That solves
everything for me.

980
00:45:09.666 --> 00:45:11.334
I'll just go down to the school

981
00:45:11.334 --> 00:45:13.878
and straighten it out
with the teacher. No problem.

982
00:45:13.878 --> 00:45:17.090
Now use head for something
other than target.

983
00:45:18.716 --> 00:45:20.760
I was only kidding about that.

984
00:45:20.760 --> 00:45:22.303
Why kidding?

985
00:45:22.303 --> 00:45:25.389
Because I'll get killed
if I show up there.

986
00:45:25.389 --> 00:45:27.017
Get killed anyway.

987
00:45:32.772 --> 00:45:34.398
Would you go with me?

988
00:45:35.775 --> 00:45:37.777
No, can't.

989
00:45:37.777 --> 00:45:39.654
Why? You said it was
a good idea, right?

990
00:45:39.654 --> 00:45:41.572
For you, good idea.

991
00:45:41.572 --> 00:45:44.617
For me,
good idea no get involved.

992
00:45:44.617 --> 00:45:46.828
Oh, but you already
are involved. I mean, you're...

993
00:45:46.828 --> 00:45:49.039
Very sorry.
What?

994
00:45:54.836 --> 00:45:57.172
Well, thanks for nothin' then.

995
00:45:57.172 --> 00:45:58.631
Thanks for nothin'.

996
00:45:58.631 --> 00:46:01.551
Like I didn't have
enough problems already.

997
00:46:01.551 --> 00:46:03.178
Now I got to carry
your weight too.

998
00:46:03.178 --> 00:46:05.346
Don't do me
any more favors, pal.

999
00:46:05.346 --> 00:46:06.597
Daniel-san?

1000
00:46:06.597 --> 00:46:07.724
What?

1001
00:46:11.435 --> 00:46:13.354
Okay, I go.

1002
00:46:15.773 --> 00:46:18.193
Well, excellent. Excellent.
Mr. Miyaji, this is great...

1003
00:46:18.193 --> 00:46:19.276
Miyagi.

1004
00:46:20.028 --> 00:46:22.155
Miyagi. Miyagi.

1005
00:46:22.155 --> 00:46:24.241
Hey, what kind of belt
do you have?

1006
00:46:24.241 --> 00:46:26.283
Canvas. You like?

1007
00:46:27.202 --> 00:46:29.495
J.C. Penney. $3.98.

1008
00:46:29.495 --> 00:46:31.455
Oh, I didn't mean a belt
like that. I meant...

1009
00:46:31.455 --> 00:46:34.751
In Okinawa, belt mean
no need rope hold up pants.

1010
00:46:34.751 --> 00:46:37.254
[LAUGHS]

1011
00:46:37.254 --> 00:46:39.089
That's... that's... that's...
That's funny.

1012
00:46:39.089 --> 00:46:40.297
Daniel-san.

1013
00:46:40.297 --> 00:46:41.424
What?

1014
00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:45.178
Karate here.

1015
00:46:46.846 --> 00:46:48.431
Karate here.

1016
00:46:49.432 --> 00:46:51.726
Karate never here.

1017
00:46:53.519 --> 00:46:55.021
You understand?

1018
00:46:56.856 --> 00:46:58.066
I think so.

1019
00:47:00.110 --> 00:47:03.029
Good night, Daniel-san.

1020
00:47:03.029 --> 00:47:05.698
Good night, Mr. Miyaji.
Miyagi. Miyagi.

1021
00:47:06.741 --> 00:47:08.659
Tomorrow morning?

1022
00:47:08.659 --> 00:47:09.827
Ten o'clock.

1023
00:47:10.703 --> 00:47:13.497
Ten o'clock.
Yeah.

1024
00:47:13.497 --> 00:47:16.042
Oh, yeah.

1025
00:47:16.042 --> 00:47:20.046
Thanks for helping me out
with my friends out there.

1026
00:47:33.434 --> 00:47:35.186
Hey, good morning,
Mr. Miyagi.

1027
00:47:35.186 --> 00:47:36.896
Oh, good morning, Daniel-san.

1028
00:47:36.896 --> 00:47:37.981
How you feel this morning?

1029
00:47:37.981 --> 00:47:39.149
I'm a little sore, really.

1030
00:47:39.149 --> 00:47:40.233
Huh.

1031
00:47:40.233 --> 00:47:42.485
You, uh, know how drive?

1032
00:47:42.485 --> 00:47:45.905
Uh, yeah, yeah, I do, really.

1033
00:47:45.905 --> 00:47:48.365
No, no, no, I'm not... I'm not
very good at it, Mr. Miyagi.

1034
00:47:48.365 --> 00:47:49.826
Me, neither.

1035
00:47:49.826 --> 00:47:51.953
Well, I really
don't have a license.

1036
00:47:51.953 --> 00:47:54.038
Me, neither.

1037
00:47:54.038 --> 00:47:55.873
I... I guess it's okay, then.

1038
00:47:55.873 --> 00:47:57.334
[ENGINE STARTING]

1039
00:48:04.841 --> 00:48:05.883
I!
ALL: Kill!

1040
00:48:05.883 --> 00:48:06.968
I!
Kill!

1041
00:48:06.968 --> 00:48:08.052
I!
Kill!

1042
00:48:08.052 --> 00:48:09.804
[CONTINUE CHANTING]

1043
00:48:32.910 --> 00:48:34.787
