That was it.

1246
00:58:55.055 --> 00:58:56.306
I don't believe you.

1247
00:58:56.306 --> 00:58:57.808
What am I gonna do,
moan and groan?

1248
00:58:57.808 --> 00:58:59.393
I don't know,
anybody else would.

1249
00:58:59.393 --> 00:59:01.311
Yeah, who'd listen anyway?

1250
00:59:01.311 --> 00:59:02.646
Me.

1251
00:59:03.689 --> 00:59:06.316
Oh, really?

1252
00:59:06.316 --> 00:59:09.402
You, uh, feel like listening
on Saturday night then?

1253
00:59:09.402 --> 00:59:10.695
Sure.

1254
00:59:10.695 --> 00:59:12.196
All right, great, great.

1255
00:59:12.196 --> 00:59:13.907
So Saturday night, we'll go out,

1256
00:59:13.907 --> 00:59:15.074
we'll have a good time,

1257
00:59:15.074 --> 00:59:17.410
we'll do whatever and, uh...

1258
00:59:17.410 --> 00:59:18.953
What is that, your address?

1259
00:59:18.953 --> 00:59:20.037
You got it.

1260
00:59:20.037 --> 00:59:21.163
[CHUCKLES]

1261
00:59:21.163 --> 00:59:22.331
Here you go.
Where is this?

1262
00:59:22.331 --> 00:59:23.708
[BELL RINGS]

1263
00:59:23.708 --> 00:59:25.960
I got to go.
Okay.

1264
00:59:25.960 --> 00:59:27.628
All right. I'll talk
to you later, then.

1265
00:59:27.628 --> 00:59:29.254
All right, great.

1266
00:59:29.254 --> 00:59:30.589
All right!

1267
00:59:33.717 --> 00:59:34.885
Hey, Mr. Harris,

1268
00:59:34.885 --> 00:59:36.386
can I talk to you for a second?

1269
00:59:36.386 --> 00:59:38.346
Daniel Larusso,
third period history class.

1270
00:59:38.346 --> 00:59:40.264
Oh, yeah.
I wanted to tell you

1271
00:59:40.264 --> 00:59:41.933
I got a lot out
of the lecture that day

1272
00:59:41.933 --> 00:59:43.935
about how the Indian
got the horse. It was great.

1273
00:59:43.935 --> 00:59:45.311
Nice to hear.

1274
00:59:45.311 --> 00:59:46.854
I... I was telling
my buddies about it,

1275
00:59:46.854 --> 00:59:48.397
but I messed it up.
So I was wondering

1276
00:59:48.397 --> 00:59:49.690
if you give us
a quick review now.

1277
00:59:49.690 --> 00:59:51.108
Oh, sure, I'm free this period.

1278
00:59:51.108 --> 00:59:52.610
Well, that's great
for me. Then...

1279
00:59:52.610 --> 00:59:55.195
ALL:
I got to go.

1280
00:59:55.195 --> 00:59:56.989
That leaves you and me, Larusso.

1281
00:59:56.989 --> 00:59:59.157
But that's all right.
I'll explain the thing to you,

1282
00:59:59.157 --> 01:00:00.701
and you can pass the information

1283
01:00:00.701 --> 01:00:01.785
on to your friends.

1284
01:00:01.785 --> 01:00:03.411
Now the Plains Indians

1285
01:00:03.411 --> 01:00:05.914
were a very primitive tribe
all over North America...

1286
01:00:17.842 --> 01:00:19.343
[SIGHS]

1287
01:00:19.343 --> 01:00:20.803
Come on, Casanova.

1288
01:00:47.202 --> 01:00:48.495
Hi.

1289
01:00:48.495 --> 01:00:49.705
Hi, how are you doin'?

1290
01:00:49.705 --> 01:00:50.789
Good.

1291
01:00:50.789 --> 01:00:52.123
You look nice.

1292
01:00:52.123 --> 01:00:53.500
Thank you.

1293
01:00:53.500 --> 01:00:55.293
